<br>
1) Where should I bind?  I've read that casters will bind in the prep area, so if they die they can mem a couple spells grab a malachite or two and run back into the battle to summon another pet or nuke.  Sounds strange but is this an approprite tactic?<br>
<br>
2) I am currently lvl 48 ... should I even bother using a pet?  I understand that pets below the lvl 49 summonings will constantly fall victim to the Dragon's fear.  If not I guess I should get lvl 49 before Sunday.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If the pet does get feared should I click my Earthen Boots to kill it off or is there no real threat of it training something back to the group?<br>
<br>
3) Which pet is good to use for Vox?  Earth for the HPs?  Water for the possible CR and average stats?  And when should the pet be summoned?  Before the fight so it can get some MR and CR buffs or after Vox has been engaged?  Also, is it normal to send the pet in right away or wait for the raid leader to call for the casters to start nuking?<br>
<br>
4) Is there some kind of a step up for the Malise line and do the Shaman's usually have a hand in it?  By step up I mean Malise first, then Malisement, then Malosi.  Does this matter or should I just cast Malisement until (or never I guess) it sticks?<br>
<br>
5) What nuke should I use?  Blaze?  Lava Bolt (assuming I get lvl 49 prior to Sunday)? SoS?<br>
<br>
If there is anything I should be aware of and have left out please feel free to insert your comments and experience.  This being my first Dragon raid I'd like to have some basic knowledge ahead of time so I don't run in there like a complete newbie.<br>
<br>
