1&gt;Bind behind the rock in the king room, back in that little nook straight out from the IG dip door.  This is a common tactic, although odds are good you'll die when you go back in.  Make sure you summon an item prior to running in, or even better have someone in your group split money.<br>
<br>
2&gt;IMHO pets are pretty worthless against vox &amp; naggy.  The stupid things always get feared.  With Vox, my pet used to get feared into random crap &amp; get killed.  Naggy my pet would spend most of the fight running.<br>
<br>
3&gt;If you feel you must use a pet, go with the water pet.  Bring it in with you when the raid leader calls for the nukers.<br>
<br>
4&gt;No step up, just go straight for Malosi.  However, odds are it won't stick &amp; you'll be better off saving your mana to nuke.<br>
<br>
5&gt;Use Blaze, Vox will just resists SoS in my experiences.  Fire on the other hand has a decent chance of messing her up.<br>
<br>
One other note, the best place you can be during this fight in my experience is DIRECTLY under Vox.  You need to be in melee range to hit her with spells anyway.<br>
<br>
As far as general resists go, try to shoot for 100+ UNBUFFED MR &amp; CR.  It's not that difficult to pull off, and it'll increase your odds of survival by a large amount.<br>
