<br>
Vox:<br>
   1) Absolutely no pets.  They get feared and can bring the bears and icy terrors.<br>
   2) You're best fire based DD or bolt.<br>
   3) You must be in melee range to land spells on dragons.<br>
   4) Absolutely no AE.<br>
<br>
Naggy:<br>
   1) Fire pet, immune to fire breath proc.<br>
   2) You're best magic based DD<br>
   3) You must be in melee range to land spells on dragons.<br>
<br>
Our last 6 Vox/Nag raids have been successful due to our exception leader and everyone LISTENING to him.  The last Nagafen went down with 22 attacking and no one died.  Our raids take an average of 2.5 hours from the first giant falling to being ported out.  <br>
<br>
The most important thing you can do is get MR and CR/FR gear.  If you aren't above 100 MR/CR unbuffed then you won't be much help.  You'll be a hinderance due to lag problems.  Another important thing is to find out the leaders rules before hand to avoid unnessecary questions.<br>
Most raid leaders don't have the mages/wizards charge and cast until the dragon is at 50% to 70% percent health.<br>
